    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain, and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-double-cod-with-herb-butter-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Strip your<strong> mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-double-cod-with-herb-butter-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>curry powder</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>on a plate</p><p>Add your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> to the plate<strong> </strong>and cover until completely coated</p><p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, then once hot, add the <strong>coated fish </strong>and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> curried fish </strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-double-cod-with-herb-butter-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, chop your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half and slice finely</p><p>Peel and slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(as finely as you can!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-double-cod-with-herb-butter-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and<strong> chopped ginger </strong>in a small bowl with the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong>, <strong>sliced shallot</strong> and your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled cucumber salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-double-cod-with-herb-butter-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped mint</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to the <strong>drained potatoes </strong>with a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> and your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 these are your<strong> herb butter potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-double-cod-with-herb-butter-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-double-cod-with-herb-butter-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>curried fish </strong>with the<strong> herb butter potatoes</strong>, the<strong> salad </strong>and<strong> quick-pickled cucumber salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> salad leaves</strong> with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
